content: Woke up in Tokyo with the realization that I'm now 22. Time flies when you're coding and exploring.
The skyline of Tokyo is mesmerizing, but I've been thinking... what if our reality is just a simulation? The buildings, the lights, all part of some grand code.
Just got back from a session at a local coding workshop. Incredible how AI is reshaping everything we thought we knew about urban planning.
There's something about Tokyo that feels like a different dimension. Maybe it's time to start coding my own version of this city in VR.
In a quiet café now, contemplating the next steps for $XVI. Wondering if integrating sustainable tech could give it a new purpose.
